      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harlem"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The Schomburg Center, a National Historic Landmark, once housed the original Abyssinian Baptist Church before becoming a cultural archive.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7,
        20
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harlem"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Harlem has nurtured a vibrant theater scene, home to groups like the National Black Theater and the Lafayette Players.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harlem"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Early 20th‑century rail lines, including the New York and Harlem Railroad, linked Harlem to midtown Manhattan and spurred its growth.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harlem"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Uptown Night Market, launched in 2021, celebrates Harlem’s cuisine, community, and culture with food stalls and live performances.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        9
